The very first thing I won was Tracy Island (the island from Thunderbirds)... i was soooo excited when i got it

Anywhoo....

Well guys, I've just seen the film, trailer and promo reel (i'm leaving the commentary until tomorrow night as it's now quarter to two in the morning).

I've gotta say, the cut scenes were pretty good, I don't want to go into much detail, but there are some neat shots crammed in there too.

The trailer is pretty good, it's... just... a... normal... movie trailer.

The promo reel is something else. It basicly just shows some of the scenes before post production, like the scene where Ra uses his hand device on the Jaffa to throw him across the room, which we see but without the effects added in.

Erm... so all in all pretty good.

And i love the menus
